712077f-a.text:
1. 33rd Street, North Side and east from Twelfth Avenue, showing the freight houses and cars belonging to the New York Central Railroad. March 17, 1929

2. The same, as seen from the foot of 33rd Street at Twelfth Avenue. June 2, 1931.

Photographs by P. L. Sperr.

710752f-a.text:
1. Twelfth Avenue, north from, but not including, the N.E. corner of 33rd Street. June 2, 1931.

2. Twelfth Avenue, north from Pier 73, North River, at 33rd Street. January 28, 1932.

3. Twelfth Avenue, north from, but not including, 33rd Street. This is nearly the same view as (1), but three years later, and from a little farther east, so that the observer is looking directly north along the western edge of the avenue itself. The West Side Elevated Highway is shown as a dark body at the extreme left. May 30, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

710751f-b.text: 12th Avenue, east side, from W. 33rd (right) to 34th Streets, showing the cleared area on the south side of W. 34th Street. At the right is the hay loft on 33rd Street, and on the left, the extensions to the old Manhattan Market. The latter are on the north side of 34th Street and are to be removed according to the New York Sun of September 16, 1938. About 1934 Views 1, 2, 3, 4. P. L. Sperr

View 1: West 33rd Street, east side, Twelfth Avenue showing New York Central Terminals and West side ramp. August 24, 1940.

P. L. Sperr.

712076f-b.text: West 33rd Street, was form a point to the east of Twelfth Avenue, showing constructional details of the steel ramp that will carry this street over the railroad yards. Eleventh Avenue will be provided for likewise and join with this at a point where Views 2 & 3 are photographed from. The outstanding structure in the background is the Empire State Building. August 24, 1940. P. L. Sperr.
